    %h3 How to use Listwerk
    %ul
      %li <strong>Create lists</strong> Type into the "New List" input and pressing the ENTER key.
      %li <strong>Create todos</strong> Type your todo into the input below a list title, then press ENTER.
      %li <strong>Sort lists and todos</strong> Drag and drop them into the desired order.
      %li <strong>Complete a todo</strong> Just click on the todo. Todos will stay on your list for 7 days after they are completed; then they'll be archived.
      %li <strong>Edit a todo</strong> Double-click on the todo; press ENTER when you're done editing.
      %li <strong>Give a todo a due date</strong> type the date in the todo with the "@" prefix. Try "@mm/dd", @monday, @wed, @tomorrow, and more...
